# DOCKER AND K3S
<h2> DOCKER </h2>

:- Docker is a containerization platform that packages applications and dependencies into lightweight containers.
  Containers run anywhere consistently.

# Key Features:

 .Image-based deployment
 .Isolation of apps
.Easy scaling and portability

<h3>Installation on AWS EC2 (Ubuntu 22.04):</h3>
# Update system
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y

# Install Docker
sudo apt install -y docker.io

# Enable Docker
sudo systemctl enable --now docker

# Add current user to docker group
sudo usermod -aG docker $USER


# K3s

What it is:

K3s is a lightweight Kubernetes distribution by Rancher.

Designed for edge, IoT, and low-resource environments.

Key Features:

Lightweight (<100 MB)

Single binary deployment

Built-in SQLite (optional)

Supports full Kubernetes API

<h3>Installation on AWS EC2 (Ubuntu 22.04):</h3>

# Install K3s
curl -sfL https://get.k3s.io | sh -

# Check status
sudo k3s kubectl get nodes

# Optional alias for kubectl
alias kubectl='sudo k3s kubectl'


# Minikube

What it is:

Minikube is a tool to run a single-node Kubernetes cluster locally.

Ideal for development and testing.

Key Features:

Supports multiple drivers (Docker, VirtualBox, KVM)

Quick start for Kubernetes experimentation

Runs locally, minimal setup

<h3>Installation on AWS EC2 (Ubuntu 22.04):</h3>
# Install dependencies
sudo apt update && sudo apt install -y curl apt-transport-https conntrack

# Install kubectl
curl -LO "https://dl.k8s.io/release/$(curl -L -s https://dl.k8s.io/release/stable.txt)/bin/linux/amd64/kubectl"
sudo install -o root -g root -m 0755 kubectl /usr/local/bin/kubectl

# Install Minikube
curl -LO https://storage.googleapis.com/minikube/releases/latest/minikube-linux-amd64
sudo install minikube-linux-amd64 /usr/local/bin/minikube

# Start Minikube (using Docker driver)
minikube start --driver=docker

# Verify
kubectl get nodes




